# Vale syncs upstream style packages (Microsoft, proselint, write-good) here via
# `vale sync`, but the project-specific vocabulary
# (config/vocabularies/CodenameOne) and our locally authored rule directory
# (CodenameOneRules) are tracked so CI and local contributors run the same word
# list and custom checks. This mirrors docs/developer-guide/.gitignore, but the
# patterns are anchored with a leading "/" because this file lives INSIDE the
# styles directory (an unanchored "*" would match at every depth and re-ignore
# the files we want to keep).
/*
!/.gitignore
!/config/
!/CodenameOneRules/
/config/*
!/config/vocabularies/
/config/vocabularies/*
!/config/vocabularies/CodenameOne/
